aaos (0.2.1-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Same-day patch closing five regressions surfaced by droplet
    QA of the v0.2.0 .deb.  v0.2.0's TOCTOU fix was broken inside
    the namespaced backend in three orthogonal ways — every
    file_read in a worker failed.
  * Fix worker rootfs missing /proc mount: added Step E2 in the
    worker setup to mount procfs at /proc with MS_NOSUID|MS_NODEV
    |MS_NOEXEC.  Without /proc the readlinkat for fd canonical-
    ization returned ENOENT.
  * Fix std::fs::read_link calling bare `readlink` syscall (denied
    by worker seccomp).  Switched path_safe to nix::fcntl::
    readlinkat which goes through the allowed `readlinkat` syscall.
  * Fix Landlock policy missing /proc read-only rule.  Added a
    PathBeneath(/proc, READ_ONLY) rule so the readlinkat is
    permitted by the worker's Landlock ruleset.
  * Fix release-mode unused-imports warning for CapabilitySnapshot
    (cfg-gated import).
  * Silence cosmetic wire_revocation_notifier duplicate-install
    warning that fired on every daemon restart.
  * Verified end-to-end: canonical fetch-HN goal in 12.6s,
    symlink read rejected with O_NOFOLLOW guard, approval-DB
    write-restart cycle works.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Sun, 26 Apr 2026 13:00:00 +0000

aaos (0.2.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Cleared-queue release.  Closes the v0.1.x carryover queue:
    push-revocation, approval persistence, canonical_for_match
    TOCTOU.  clone3 seccomp tightening (Bug 19) was filed as
    structurally infeasible and moved to docs/ideas.md.
  * Push-revocation protocol (Bugs 11 + 18): CapabilityRegistry
    now publishes revocations to a pluggable RevokeNotifier;
    aaos-backend-linux wires SessionMapNotifier to push
    Request::RevokeToken frames to active worker sessions.
    revoke_all_for_agent also fires the notifier.  Worker
    sessions now hold a session-level CapabilityRegistry.
  * Approval queue persistence: SQLite store at
    /var/lib/aaos/approvals.db (override AAOS_APPROVAL_DB).
    Pending approvals survive daemon restart.
  * canonical_for_match TOCTOU: file_read / file_write /
    file_edit / file_list / file_read_many / grep all migrated
    to O_NOFOLLOW + /proc/self/fd/<fd> capability check.  The
    leaf-component symlink-swap race that Round 4 + 5 self-
    reflection runs identified is structurally closed.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Sun, 26 Apr 2026 12:30:00 +0000

aaos (0.1.7-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix Bug 27 (high): both spawn paths in spawn_tool.rs issued
    child capability tokens with Constraints::default(), silently
    dropping parent max_invocations / rate_limit / expiry.  Phase
    A's run-1 finding #3 had regressed in a later refactor when
    the spawn paths needed capability substitution that the
    existing CapabilityToken::narrow() couldn't provide.  Fix:
    new narrow_with_capability() method that substitutes the
    narrower capability AND inherits parent constraints
    atomically.  Both spawn paths refactored to use it.
  * Surfaced by round-5 v0.1.6 self-reflection on a fresh droplet.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Sat, 26 Apr 2026 11:30:00 +0000

aaos (0.1.6-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix Bug 26 (medium): charge capability use BEFORE tool
    invocation, not after.  The Bug 10 v0.1.1 fix had recorded
    use post-invoke; if the token expired or was revoked between
    permits() and the post-invoke record, the tool had already
    run with no count recorded — a free invocation past
    max_invocations.  New order: authorize_and_record before
    invoke; on failure the tool doesn't run.  Charge-on-attempt
    semantics, fail-closed.
  * Filed two more findings to docs/ideas.md as deferred-
    hardening entries (canonical_for_match TOCTOU, McpMessage
    sender authentication).

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Fri, 25 Apr 2026 17:10:00 +0000

aaos (0.1.5-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix Bug 24 (low — doc correctness): broker_session.rs module
    doc made a false security claim about "seccomp denying dup2"
    — actually dup3 is allowed and dup2 falls through to EPERM.
    Corrected doc to reflect the real mitigations (Landlock +
    user-ns + session-id correlation).  No runtime change.
  * Fix Bug 25 (low-medium): registry.rs::stop held a DashMap
    shard guard across an mpsc::send().await — could stall any
    other task on the same shard under buffer pressure.  Cloned
    the channel sender before the guard scope ends.
  * Disproved a deadlock claim against the v0.1.3 Bug 21 fix
    via source review; Bug 21 fix is correct.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Fri, 25 Apr 2026 16:50:00 +0000

aaos (0.1.4-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix Bug 22 (high): workspace GC follows symlinks, allowing
    privilege escalation.  An agent with FileWrite to its workspace
    could plant a symlink that the GC would chase to delete a
    target under aaos:aaos.  Fix: DirEntry::file_type() instead of
    path.is_dir(); explicitly reject symlinks.
  * Fix Bug 23 (medium): approval requests had no timeout; agent
    awaiting approval blocked forever on operator absence and the
    pending entry leaked.  Fix: tokio::time::timeout(1h) around
    the response oneshot; remove + deny on expiry.
  * Triaged two more findings (CapabilityToken::permits TOCTOU,
    approval-queue persistence) — neither ships in v0.1.4.

