aaos (0.1.1-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix Bug 12: glob_matches separator-boundary check. Pattern /data/*
    no longer matches /data-foo/x or /data_foo/x.
  * Fix Bug 15: pending_responses RAII cleanup in send_and_wait. Adds
    MessageRouter::cancel_pending; a guard removes leaked entries on
    route error or timeout.
  * Fix Bug 16: SqliteMemoryStore::store now wraps DELETE+INSERT in an
    explicit rusqlite transaction. A failed INSERT no longer permanently
    deletes the replaced record.
  * Fix Bug 10: ToolInvocation::invoke now calls authorize_and_record
    after a successful tool invocation. max_invocations constraints are
    enforced at the invocation layer.
  * Narrow Bug 11: resolve_tokens filters revoked and expired tokens
    before forwarding to workers. Tokens revoked mid-call are still
    honoured by in-flight worker invocations (residual race; full fix
    requires push-revocation protocol, queued for v0.2.x).

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Fri, 25 Apr 2026 14:00:00 +0000

aaos (0.1.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Architecture: both orchestration modes (plan/decompose and
    persistent/direct) now route through the unified PlanExecutor.
    The Bootstrap persistent agent is no longer used for per-submit
    goals.
  * Each subtask now runs as a full multi-turn agent. Iteration budget
    is set by role.orchestration.max_iterations (default 50) instead
    of the old retry.max_attempts+10 formula (default ~12).
  * Bug 9 closed: fallback_generalist_plan deleted. A malformed Planner
    response now propagates as a correctable error through the replan
    loop; after max_replans exhausted the run fails cleanly with no
    hallucinated report on disk.
  * New role YAML fields: orchestration.max_iterations (u32, default 50)
    and require_declared_output (bool, default false). fetcher role sets
    require_declared_output: true.
  * New SubtaskOutputMissing advisory audit event when a subtask finishes
    without writing its declared output and require_declared_output is
    false.
  * Classifier output changed from plan/persistent to decompose/direct;
    fallback on LLM error is now direct (was plan). Wire API preserved.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 22:00:00 +0000

aaos (0.0.5-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Feature: agentd submit now auto-classifies the goal and routes
    it to plan mode (Planner + PlanExecutor DAG) or persistent mode
    (Bootstrap persistent agent) automatically.  A cheap single-shot
    LLM call inspects the goal text before any agent work begins.
    Operators can force a mode with --orchestration [plan|persistent];
    the classifier is bypassed.  Surfaces which mode was picked via
    a structured audit event and a journald log line.
  * Previously a missing role catalog silently fell through to the
    Bootstrap path; plan mode now errors cleanly with a pointer
    at journalctl.

